<strong>About eFounders</strong></p>
<p>
<a href="http://e-founders.com/">eFounders</a> is a startup studio focused on building fast-growing SaaS technology companies. We believe that with simple ideas, great talents, some money and a lot of effort, we can build prosperous companies. Our goal is to co-found two companies per year and to help all our existing companies grow faster by mutualising ressources.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
So far, eFounders launched 4 companies:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<a href="https://eu.mailjet.com/">Mailjet</a></li>
<li>
<a href="http://fr.textmaster.com/">Textmaster</a></li>
<li>
<a href="https://en.mention.net/">Mention</a></li>
<li>
<a href="http://www.pressking.com/">Pressking</a></li>
<li>
Soon more :-)</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>About the opportunity</strong></p>
<p>
We are seeking a strong profile in Communication and Marketing with Project Management skills to help us spread the word about our companies and eFounders. You will work for multiple companies on multiple projects at the same time.The job is highly independent job, with a proactive approach needed. You will be working in a fast-moving environment with passionate people and learn from experienced and successful entrepreneurs.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Increase brand awareness about our companies and eFounders by doing inbound marketing, partnerships, sponsoring, writing white papers, contacting journalists, community management, etc;</li>
<li>
Develop the eFounders family by organising online activities &amp; offline events;</li>
<li>
Manage the Startup Pack initiative by sourcing partners, negotiating offers, managing resources, handling press campaign, etc</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The ideal candidate will have</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
1-2 years experience of com &amp; marketing, social media, project management</li>
<li>
Native english + french speaker with strong writing skills</li>
<li>
Dynamic, enthusiast and pro-active</li>
<li>
Loves social media (Twitter, Facebook, Quora, Reddit, Hacker News,...)</li>
<li>
Interest in startups, social media, SaaS companies</li>
<li>
Always looking to go the extra-mile &amp; highly self-driven as it&rsquo;s an independent role</li>
<li>
Based in Brussels</li>
</ul>
